			<div class="content" id="post-content-1589856">
									

<p>Well, this one is right up my alley. I prefer Lynchian weirdness to straightforward sinister any day, <em>and</em> I was a Lit major. I have a lot of not entirely positive feelings about Faulkner, but the careful details you've written into this are pretty nifty. This is a very multi-layered SCP, tone-wise, and I personally found the mood set by the &quot;non-anomalous&quot; story was a clever set-up for the coded section.</p>
<p>In short: I think this was a risky SCP to write and won't be universally appealing, but I am impressed by the careful crafting and it hits all my literary kinks. This is more surrealism than horror, but I think that has its place on the mainlist. We get technological/sciency SCPs pretty often&#8212; it's cool to see one that requires &quot;personnel with an educational background in literary criticism and/or cryptography&quot;, it's a reminder of the breadth of content the Foundation has to be prepared to deal with.</p>

							</div>

								
					
